{"article_id":"r0kivB9l6PUqHKHC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Welcome to November .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Earlier in the week , one of the oldest and most respected polling firms","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"in America","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"-- Gallup --","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"produced results","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"based on thousands of voter contacts","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"indicating","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that Mitt Romney is leading in national early voting by roughly six percentage points .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Last night , another venerable polling outfit confirmed Gallup 's findings with a survey of its own .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"From Pew Research :","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"The Pew Research Center survey found","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"that the race is even among all likely voters nationwide","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"( 47 % Obama , 47 % Romney ) .","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"Unlike the last campaign , the race also is close among voters","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"who say","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"they have already voted .","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"In the poll ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"conducted Oct. 24-28 ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"19 % of likely voters say","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"they have already voted ;","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"that is unchanged from the same week in the 2008 campaign","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"( Oct. 23-26 , 2008 ) .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Currently , Romney holds a seven-point edge among early voters","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"( 50 % to 43 % ) ;","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"because of the small sample ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"this lead is not statistically significant .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"At this point four years ago , Obama led John McCain by 19 points","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"( 53 % to 34 % )","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"among early voters .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"The overall sample was roughly 1700 voters , only about half the size of Gallup 's pool ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"but resulting in nearly the exact same early voting outcome .","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"In this case , Romney by seven .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Gallup found","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"that Obama led McCain by 15 points in early tallies at this stage in 2008 ;","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Pew puts the gap at 19 points ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"so their 2012 numbers represent a 26-point swing to the GOP ticket .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"That 's ... not insignificant .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"But what about in the swing states ?","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"The Washington Post reports","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that Obama has the lead in most","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"( but not all )","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"of the contested battlegrounds ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"but that Romney is hugely outpacing McCain 's 2008 numbers .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"In brief , Republicans are narrowing the gap in Nevada , North Carolina and Iowa","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"( where one new state poll gives Romney a slight overall lead ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"while another shows","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Obama winning ) .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Romney is doing quite well in Colorado ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"where the GOP is actually leading Democrats , very much unlike last cycle .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"In Florida , Democrats have a small edge in the early totals ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"but nowhere near their 2008 levels :","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Democrats hold a narrow lead","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"( 43 percent to 41 percent )","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"and are not on pace","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"to match their 46-37 advantage from 2008 .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"We are through four days of the eight-day period for in-person early voting ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"while Democrats gained big on the first two days","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"( Saturday and Sunday ) ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"they were unable to keep that pace on Monday and Tuesday .","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"Democrat netted 73,000 vote from the first two days ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"but gained 28,000 votes on Monday and just 16,000 votes on Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Meanwhile , Republicans keep building their absentee lead ,","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"which stands at 70,000 votes .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"While Democrats won the combined early vote","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"( absentee plus in-person )","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"by more than 360,000 votes in 2008 ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"they currently lead by about 49,000 .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"That edge will grow over the next four days","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"as Democrats build their in-person early voting lead","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"( many more people vote in-person than absentee ) ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"but it ' s unlikely to approach anywhere near 360,000 .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"The Romney campaign said today","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"that they expect to win Florida 's election day voters by double digits .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"In Virginia , counties","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"that Obama won last time","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"have seen a dramatic drop-off in absentee balloting ;","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"absentee `` turnout '' in Republican areas has slowed a bit ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"but not as much as Democrat territory .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Finally , there 's Ohio .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Public polling shows Obama with a large lead ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"but there 's no way","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"to verify that .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Republicans say","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"the raw numbers do n't bear out that big Obama advantage :","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"\" The Gallup numbers nationally confirm","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"what we think","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"is happening here in Ohio , \"","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"says one Romney official .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"\" It ' s two things .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"One , their margin of victory in early voting is greatly diminished -","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"drastically diminished .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"And two , they are having a very difficult time","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"generating enthusiasm among young people. \"","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"Asked for evidence","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"to support those claims ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"the official cited a Romney tally","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"showing","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"absentee and early voting is ten percent higher in counties","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"McCain won in 2008","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"than in counties","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"Obama won .","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"He also pointed to sluggish early voting in the Toledo area ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"which Obama won in ' 08 ,","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"and particularly energetic early voting in the Cincinnati area ,","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"which McCain won .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"In addition , the official argues","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"that Republicans are \" outperforming our share of voter registration in absentee requests and early votes \"","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"and that the GOP has \" closed the gap on Democrats ' historical absentee and early vote advantage for 20 of the past 21 days . \"","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"Has that gap closed enough","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"to stem Obama 's pre-election day tide","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"and tee up a Romney win at the ballot box day-of ?","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"The answer to that question , ladies and gents , may very well determine the 2012 presidential election .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"One alternate route to 270 for Romney involves Wisconsin ,","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"which was tied as of late last week .","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"Then came Marquette 's latest poll ,","depth":6},{"id":116,"text":"which shows Obama ahead by eight","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"-- a seven-point jump in approximately one week .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"Wisconsin insiders smell a sampling rat .","depth":5},{"id":119,"text":"Even so ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"just when you think","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Wisconsin may be slipping away","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"( I 've heard the opposite from folks on the ground there , by the way ) ,","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"an elected Democrat says this :","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"Hancock even broke news on that Wisconsin trip ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"telling voters","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"if the election were to be held right now","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"the president would lose Wisconsin and its coveted 10 electoral votes . ...","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"\" We have not turned out the vote early , \"","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"Hancock told the newspaper .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"\" The suburbs and rural parts of Wisconsin","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"- the Republican base -","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"are voting .","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"President Obama ' s base has yet to go vote .","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"We ' ve got to get our people to go vote . \"","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"No , no !","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"False ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"protests Team Obama .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"I guess we 'll wait and see","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"wo n't we ?","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"UPDATE -","depth":3},{"id":141,"text":"Rasmussen still has the Badger State race knotted at 49 apiece .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":283,"left":0